  <summary date="2021-10-20T18:03:15Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Performing Artist Tax Parity Act of 2021

This bill modifies the tax deduction for the expenses of performing artists (including commissions paid to managers or agents) to provide for a phaseout of such deduction for taxpayers whose adjusted gross income exceeds $100,000 ($200,000 for joint return filers). The $100,000 phaseout threshold is adjusted for inflation annually for taxable years beginning after 2021.</summary>
